The evidence with the title 'U.S. health care: Highest in the world in cost, 37th in performance ... ' says Mar 26, 2012  ... The U.S. spends the second greatest amount of gdp for health care among all members of the United Nations , topped only by East Timor . For its money, the U.S. obtains health outcomes that are near the bottom of the OECD rankings , and , in fact, rival some of the outcomes of Third World countries. 
